India, Thailand, Malaysia, Japan: Asian Bonds and Foreign Exchange Preview

-- B y   V .   R a m a k r i s h n a n
-- 
2011-05-02T23:12:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/india-thailand-malaysia-japan-asian-bonds-and-foreign-exchange-preview.html
The following events and economic
reports may influence trading in  Asia ’s bonds and currencies
today. Bond yields and exchange rates are from the previous
trading session unless stated otherwise.  Japan: Japan’s financial markets will be closed for a
national holiday.  The yield on the 1.3 percent government bond due March 2021
was 1.20 percent, according to Japan Bond Trading Co., the
nation’s largest interdealer debt broker. The yen traded at
81.20 per dollar at 7:59 a.m. in  Tokyo .  India : The  Reserve Bank  of India will increase the
repurchase auction rate by 25 basis points to 7 percent,
according to 18 of 25 economists surveyed by Bloomberg News
before a policy review today. Seven predicted a 50-basis point
increase.  The yield on the 7.80 percent bond due April 2021 was 8.14
percent. The rupee was at 44.355 per dollar.  Thailand : The Bank of Thailand will sell 97 billion baht
($3.2 billion) of 27-, 90, 181- and 363-day bills. The
government will sell 5 billion baht of bonds due 2041.  The yield on the 3.125 percent debt due December 2015 was
3.31 percent. The baht was at 29.88 per dollar.  Malaysia: The central bank will sell 2 billion ringgit
($675 million) of 91-day notes and 1 billion ringgit of 210-day
notes today.  The yield on the benchmark 4.16 percent note due July 2021
was at 4.04 percent. The ringgit was at 2.9630.  To contact the reporter on this story:
